ReadBoot Branding Standards
1. Visual Identity: "Futurist Carton"
Aesthetic: High-contrast, editorial cartoon style with thick linework.

Linework: Use consistent 4px solid charcoal borders ($ref-color-charcoal) for all primary containers and buttons.

Corner Radius: Use 12px for a rounded, playful feel that mimics hand-drawn ink art.

2. Design Tokens (Source of Truth)
Always use tokens from @repo/ui/src/styles/variables/ instead of hardcoded values:

Colors:

Background: $sys-color-paper-bg (#FAF9F6)

Ink/Text: $sys-color-ink-text (#36454F)

Action: $sys-color-action-primary (#DC143C)

Typography:

Headlines: Baloo 2 (Font-weight: 700)

Body: Inter (Academic/Clean)

3. Naming Convention (BEM)
Always use the Block-Element-Modifier syntax:

Blocks: .button, .card, .masthead

Modifiers: .button--action, .fx--glitch

4. Interactive Effects
The Glitch: Apply .fx--glitch to symbolize "critical system breaks." Use the keyframes defined in @_animations.scss.

Hover States: Interactive elements must feel "bouncy." Use a 1.05 scale transform with a bouncy cubic-bezier easing.

Grid Layout: For long-form text, implement newspaper-inspired column layouts using column-count.

5. Technical Requirements
Format: Use SCSS Modules only (.module.scss). No Styled-Components.

Auto-Injection: Variables are injected globally via next.config.ts. Do NOT manually @import or @use variables inside component SCSS modules unless custom resolution fails.
